# The ToS-gate manifest fixture is cryptographically signed — git's autocrlf
# line-ending conversion (the default on Windows, including GitHub's hosted
# Windows runners) silently rewrites LF to CRLF on checkout, corrupting the
# exact bytes the signature was computed over and failing verification with
# ManifestSignatureError. -text disables that conversion unconditionally,
# regardless of the checking-out machine's core.autocrlf setting.
gateway/policy/fixtures/** -text
